			    STPJS 305</div>
  <p class="cont">derstand the three principal rounds of Jacob&rsquo;s ladder<span class="footRef">1</span>&mdash;the telestial, the terrestrial, and the celestial
  glories or kingdoms,<span class="footRef">2</span> where Paul saw and heard things which were not lawful for him to utter.<span class="footRef">3</span> I
  could explain a hundred fold more<span class="footRef">4</span> than I ever have of the glories of the kingdoms manifested to me
  in the vision,<span class="footRef">5</span> were I permitted, and were the people prepared to receive them.<span class="footRef">6</span></p>
  <p class="std">The Lord deals with this people as a tender parent<span class="footRef">7</span> with a child, communicating light and
  intelligence and the knowledge of his ways<span class="footRef">8</span> as they can bear it.<span class="footRef">9</span> The inhabitants of the earth are
  asleep;<span class="footRef">10</span> they know not the day of their visitation.<span class="footRef">11</span> The Lord hath set the bow in the cloud<span class="footRef">12</span> for a
  sign that while it shall be seen, seed time and harvest, summer and winter shall not fail; but when
  it shall disappear, woe to that generation, for behold the end cometh quickly.<span class="footRef">13</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Calling and Election to Be Made Sure</div>
  <p class="std">Contend earnestly<span class="footRef">14</span> for the like precious<span class="footRef">15</span> faith<span class="footRef">16</span> with the Apostle Peter, &ldquo;and add to your faith
  virtue,&rdquo; knowledge, temperance, patience, godliness, brotherly kindness, charity; &ldquo;for if these things
  be in you, and abound, they make you that ye shall neither be barren nor unfruitful in the knowledge
  of our Lord Jesus Christ.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">17</span> Another point, after having all these qualifications, he lays this
  injunction upon the people &ldquo;to make your calling and election sure.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">18</span> He is emphatic upon this
  subject&mdash;after adding all this virtue, knowledge,<span class="footRef">19</span> etc., &ldquo;Make your calling and election sure.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">20</span>
  What is the secret&mdash;the starting point? &ldquo;According as His divine power hath given unto us all things
  that pertain unto life and godliness.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">21</span> How did he obtain all things? Through the knowledge of Him
  who hath called him.<span class="footRef">22</span> There could not anything be given, pertaining to life and godliness,<span class="footRef">23</span> without
  knowledge. Woe!  woe!  woe to Christendom!&mdash;especially the divines and priests if this be true.</p>
  <p class="std">Salvation is for a man to be saved from all his enemies;<span class="footRef">24</span> for until a man can triumph over
  death,<span class="footRef">25</span> he is not saved. A knowledge of the priesthood<span class="footRef">26</span> alone will do this.</p>
